# 7-Ply Discord Bot Configuration

## Required Environment Variables
DISCORD_TOKEN=your-bot-token-here

## Command Management
# Set SYNC_COMMANDS=true only when you need to update slash commands
# Keep it false for normal operation to avoid Discord rate limits
SYNC_COMMANDS=false

## Bot Permissions Required
# The bot needs these permissions in your Discord server:
# - Send Messages
# - Use Slash Commands  
# - Manage Messages (for admin commands and slowmode)
# - Manage Channels (for temp voice channels)
# - Manage Roles (for reaction roles)
# - Add Reactions (for suggestions voting and reaction roles)
# - Create Public Threads (for suggestions)
# - View Channels
# - Read Message History

## Data Storage
# Bot data is stored in the data/ directory:
# - data/servers/{guild_id}.json - Per-server configurations
# - data/users/{user_id}.json - User ranking data
# - data/reaction_roles.json - Reaction role message tracking